deposit(address).details: Collect all fee of transactions from the current block and deposit it to the contract

params.valAddr: The validator address who produced the current block

enterMaintenance().details: Enter maintenance for current validators. refer to https://github.com/bnb-chain/BEPs/blob/master/BEP127.md

exitMaintenance().details: Exit maintenance for current validators. refer to https://github.com/bnb-chain/BEPs/blob/master/BEP127.md

params.index: The index of the validator in `currentValidatorSet`(from 0 to `currentValidatorSet.length-1`)

updateValidatorSetV2(address[],uint64[],.details: Update validator set method after fusion fork.      * Malaketh-Layered: If empty arrays are passed, automatically fetch validator data from StakeHub

canEnterMaintenance(uint256).notice: Return whether the validator at index could enter maintenance

getCurrentValidatorIndex(address).notice: Return the index of the validator in `currentValidatorSet`(from 0 to `currentValidatorSet.length-1`)

getIncoming(address).notice: Return the current incoming of the validator

getLivingValidators().notice: Return the vote address and consensus address of the validators in `currentValidatorSet` that are not jailed

getMiningValidators().notice: Return the vote address and consensus address of mining validators     * Mining validators are block producers in the current epoch including most of the cabinets and a few of the candidates

getValidators().notice: Return the consensus address of the validators in `currentValidatorSet` that are not jailed and not maintaining

getWorkingValidatorCount().notice: Return the number of mining validators. The function name is misleading, it should be `getMiningValidatorCount`. But it's kept for compatibility.

isCurrentValidator(address).notice: Return whether the validator is a working validator(not jailed or maintaining) by consensus address Will return false if the validator is not in `currentValidatorSet`

isWorkingValidator(uint256).notice: Return whether the validator is a working validator(not jailed or maintaining) by index
